Price as on 01.59.00 PM, Click on company names for their live prices.
As Indian equities continued their upward trajectory at the start of the week, attention now turns to the symbolic Muhurat Trading session scheduled for today, marking the beginning of Samvat 2082. This annual ritual, deeply rooted in market tradition, offers investors an auspicious window to initiate fresh positions for the new Hindu financial year. Read More
Indian markets extended positive momentum, driven by better-than-expected Q2 results from major companies and festival optimism. Positive global cues further bolstered investor sentiment, with easing trade narratives between the US-China and rise in European markets led by defense stocks. In today's session, trading will be symbolic and brief for an hour or so to mark Diwali. Read More
As Indian markets head into Diwali 2025, domestic sentiment has strengthened on easing global headwinds and resilient macro fundamentals. Brokerages see indices poised for a breakout backed by broad-based strength across banking sectors. Here are seven festive-season picks from the financial sector that reflect this optimism, each positioned for fresh momentum into Samvat 2082 Read More
As Samvat 2082 dawns with the auspicious Muhurat trading session today, Dalal Street is set to sparkle with festive optimism. Despite global uncertainties, analysts expect the special one-hour window to reflect India’s resilient growth story, backed by robust corporate earnings, steady domestic liquidity and upbeat investor sentiment. Brokerage houses have lined up their top stock picks across sectors — from banks and IT to autos — offering a mix of stability and strong return potential for the new trading year. Read More
With the beginning of a new Samvat 2082, brokerages InCred Equities and Religare Broking have identified 5 stocks each to buy this Diwali. While InCred has suggested techno-funda pick, Religare has recommended fundamental socks. The stocks are from varied sectors. Read More
- Kotak: Adani Ports, Acutaas Chemical, Cummins, Eternal, ICICI Bank, M&M, Reliance.
- LKP: Bajaj Finance, SBI Cards, Divi’s Lab, SBI, Nykaa, Swiggy.
- Incred: Apollo Tyres, Canara Bank, Nesco, Sandur Manganese, Premier Explosives.
- PSU banks: 65% chance of 9% weekly gain, 18% monthly gain
- Metals: 60% probability of 4% weekly, 8.5% monthly gain
- Realty & Pharma: historically weaker; Realty may fall ~5% next week, Pharma ~3–4%
Historical Trends
- Nifty closed higher 80% of Muhurat sessions (avg gain 0.5%)
- Midcap & Smallcap indices rise ~90% of the time (avg gains 0.7–1%)
- Positive pre-Muhurat week → Nifty gains 0.6% during session, ~2% following week
- Pre-open session: 1:30 PM – 1:45 PM
- Main trading window: 1:45 PM – 2:45 PM
- Closing session: 2:55 PM – 3:05 PM
- Trade modifications: Till 3:15 PM
- This brief yet symbolic hour ushers in Samvat 2082, setting the tone for another year of wealth and wisdom.
For the first time in decades, India’s stock exchanges are moving the sacred Diwali Muhurat Trading window to an afternoon slot (1:45 pm–2:45 pm on Oct 21) — marking a rare shift in the market’s festive ritual as Samvat 2082 begins.

